{"word":"συναινέω","slug":"συναινέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συναινέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>έσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to join in praising</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to consent</i>, <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ς. τινί</el> <i>to agree with</i> a person, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to agree to, promise</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <i>to grant at once</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to agree</i> or <i>consent</i> to do, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}